	â€¢	Source of Funds â€“ Where the money originally comes from.
	â€¢	Purpose of Funds â€“ The reason for the transaction.
	â€¢	Where the Funds Have Come From â€“ The movement of funds before the transaction.
	â€¢	Rationale for the Transaction â€“ Why the transaction is justified.

We have now automated this process by extracting and analyzing these parameters programmatically.

Key Enhancements & Automation Steps

1. Timeliness Check (Overdue Analysis)

Previously, overdue transactions were identified manually. We automated this by introducing a day counter condition:
âœ… If the transaction is delayed beyond 14 days, it is automatically tagged as overdue.

This eliminates the need for manual review of each transactionâ€™s timeliness.

2. Commentary Quality Assessment

When analyzing the comments, we noticed that users enter these four key parameters in different ways, sometimes using abbreviations or informal terms.

To handle this, we developed a custom text extraction process using Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques.

Challenges We Addressed:
	â€¢	Comments were written inconsistently (e.g., â€œSOF:â€, â€œSOW:â€, â€œSource of Wealthâ€)
	â€¢	Some details were mixed with other parameters
	â€¢	Keywords could be attached to other words without spaces

To solve this, we built a text preprocessing and extraction mechanism that:
âœ” Standardizes text formats (removing extra spaces, handling abbreviations)
âœ” Extracts relevant phrases dynamically (detects sentences related to each parameter)
âœ” Ensures completeness by checking if all four parameters are present

3. Advanced Text Extraction & Processing

We developed a custom rule-based extraction engine to capture key details from the comments.

How It Works:
âœ… First, we clean and normalize the text (removing unwanted characters, fixing missing spaces).
âœ… Next, we search for predefined patterns that indicate each parameter.
âœ… If a parameter is found, we capture its full statement until either:
	â€¢	A full stop (.)
	â€¢	The start of another key parameter

For example, consider this original comment:

	â€œSource of funds: The source of funds for this payment was Ram and Sita investment portfolio with Brown Shipley. Where have funds come from: Cash from settled investment sales at Brown Shipley.â€

Extracted Results:
âœ” Source of Funds â†’ The source of funds for this payment was Ram and Sita investment portfolio with Brown Shipley.
âœ” Where the Funds Have Come From â†’ Cash from settled investment sales at Brown Shipley.

This ensures high accuracy while keeping the information structured.

4. Quality Scoring Mechanism

Once all four commentary parameters are extracted, we assign a Commentary Quality Score based on completeness:

Parameters Found	Commentary Score (%)
4 Parameters (All Found)	100% (Likely Complete)
3 Parameters	75%
2 Parameters	50% (Needs Review)
1 Parameter	25%
0 Parameters	0% (Likely Incomplete)
No parameters + Short Comment	Not enough information

This automates the evaluation process and eliminates manual subjectivity in assessing completeness.

5. Financial Match Check

To enhance validation, we also extract financial values from the comments and compare them with the transaction amount.
âœ… If the extracted amount matches the recorded transaction value, we flag it as a valid match.
âœ… If no match is found, it suggests potential missing or incorrect information.

6. Overdue & Defaulter Analysis (Pivot Insights)

Using the extracted insights, we created Pivot Table-based views for:
âœ… Overdue Analysis â€“ Identifying repeated defaulters who frequently miss deadlines.
âœ… AML Risk Segmentation â€“ Tracking overdue cases across High Risk, PEP (Politically Exposed Persons), and Standard Risk categories.
âœ… Banker Performance View â€“ Highlighting how individual bankers manage large transactions.

